Vid wasnt that bad, just was in need of some TLC....Ran some video analysis passes, and also ran yuv/rgb pro-filer. RGB and coloring was off, vid seemed washed out and lifeless at times, so we straightened that out best we could. Gamma and black levels were also fixed accordingly, fixed slight flicker it had in parts of vid too. Did a slight re-size to get the pic tight, and a 3-way noise reducer to clean up vid with a slight re sharp as well. Cut vid into a few pieces, then Cropped and used perspective to get vid straightened out right. Adjusted the AR as well, vid seemed a bit off at times with fat faces..lol....... Few other ticks as well.......
       The audio was decent for cam, but did have some clipping and some static noise so we cut the audio into sections and worked each one accordingly...The low end Hz levels were outta control at times overpowering the track, so we had to eliminate certain frequency ranges and cap others, in order to get it in line...also inserted a few band passes[dynamic] to keep the remaining bass smooth  and minimize distortion levels.  Removed the slight hiss that was present , smoothed out the track and set peak gain filters to keep the loud parts level as to hear dialogue better during loud sections, over all sound is clear and level.... Hopefully an improvement.....Finally, synced audio back to video and done! As always, we tried our best to improve this all-around....Hope some of you appreciate it..and those who do not, maybe u should step up and have something to offer us instead..... thanks to all of you who support us!
